The health care sector and, on a broader scale, societies across the globe recognize the magnitude of the current and projected chronic disease burden we face.

Poor lifestyle habits are at the center of this crisis;

poor CRF and PI are core components of the unhealthy lifestyle phenotype that portend a significantly higher risk for chronic disease (153,154). As elucidated in other sections of this review, high CRF and PA portend enormous health benefits. The evidence is so overwhelming that there is now recognition that "exercise is medicine" (2,155). In fact, the case can be made that, more broadly, movement is medicine (i.e., sitting as little as possible, taking as many steps as you can every day, and participating in a regular exercise program) is an even more appro- Table 4 summarizes key recommendations provided in this AHA scientific statement (123).
